commentary.comment: The first half of this match is about to start.
What a chance! Benjamin Moukandjo (Lorient) rises high to connect with the resulting corner inside the box, but his bullet header rattles the right post.
Clement Turpin shows a yellow card to Adama Niane (Troyes) for his blatant foul.
The match has reached half-time.
The second half has just started.
Substitution. Wesley Lautoa makes his way off the pitch and Jimmy Cabot (Lorient) comes on as his replacement.
Stephane Darbion (Troyes) is booked after bringing down an opponent. Clement Turpin had an easy-decision to make.
It must be a yellow card. It is. Jeremy Cordoval (Troyes) receives the caution after an awful tackle.
The referee signals that it is time for a substitution and Carlos Miguel Cafu (Lorient) will replace Walid Mesloub.
Substitution. Adama Niane did his best and is replaced by Benjamin Nivet (Troyes).
This yellow card was deserved. The tackle by Romain Philippoteaux (Lorient) was quite harsh and Clement Turpin didn't hesitate to show him a yellow card.
Romain Philippoteaux will be replaced by Jeremie Aliadiere (Lorient).
Jean-Louis Garcia prepares a substitution. Stephane Darbion is replaced by Alois Confais (Troyes).
Substitution. Jonathan Tinhan (Troyes) on for Samuel Grandsir.
Clement Turpin is looking at his watch and immediately ends this match.
The match has just started.

Kylian Mbappe (Monaco) blows a clear opportunity to score a goal. He was one-on-one with Stephane Ruffier inside the six-yard box and attempted to put the ball into the right side of the target, but was denied by a great save. Monaco force a corner. They send men into the box.
Goal - 1:0! Falcao tees up Kylian Mbappe (Monaco) inside the box and he rolls the ball into the bottom left corner and past Stephane Ruffier.
Christophe Galtier is forced to make a change. Digbo Maiga is unable to continue due to injury, Jeremy Clement (St Etienne) comes on.
There will be nothing more to see in the first half. The whistle blowing of Clement Turpin has ended it.
The second half gets underway.
Falcao (Monaco) rises highest from the corner to head at goal, but his low effort towards the middle of the goal is comfortably saved by the goalkeeper. Monaco win a corner.

Arnaud Nordin (St Etienne) goes on a mazy run, skips past two defenders and pulls the trigger in front of the keeper. Danijel Subasic makes a great save to stop the effort going low into the middle of the goal.
A yellow card for a tackle by Bernardo Silva (Monaco). Clement Turpin doesn't hesitate at all to make this decision.
That's the end of the game for Alexander Soderlund, who is replaced by Romain Hamouma (St Etienne).
Leonardo Jardim prepares a substitution. Bernardo Silva is replaced by Valere Germain (Monaco).
Valere Germain (Monaco) makes a yard for himself inside the box after an accurate pass and takes a shot that goes just wide of the left post.
The foul by Leo Lacroix (St Etienne) is worthy of a card and a yellow is duly shown by Clement Turpin.
Fabien Lemoine will be replaced by Kenny Rocha Santos (St Etienne).
A substitution has been made. Falcao is replaced by Guido Carrillo (Monaco).
Leonardo Jardim has decided to make a change. Andrea Raggi (Monaco) replaces Kylian Mbappe.
Goal! Valere Germain (Monaco) fires home from very close range after latching on to a pass from Thomas Lemar. The score is 2:0.
The match has just finished.
The first half has just begun.
It's a goal! Falcao (Monaco) gets on the end of a pass and it allows him to finish into an empty net with a close-range header. The score has changed to 1:0.
Goal! Bernardo Silva (Monaco) fires home from very close range after latching on to a pass from Kylian Mbappe. The score is 2:0.
Benoit Bastien has ended the first half by blowing the whistle.
The players are back out on the pitch following the half-time break and the second half is about to start.
This yellow card was deserved. The tackle by Jemerson (Monaco) was quite harsh and Benoit Bastien didn't hesitate to show him a yellow card.
Naim Sliti (Lille) is shown a yellow card for a late challenge.
Benoit Bastien shows a yellow card to Rio Mavuba (Lille) for his blatant foul.
Substitution. Nicolas De Preville (Lille) on for Ricardo Kishna.
Falcao (Monaco) converts a killer cross with a curling shot inside the right post! What a perfect finish!
Franck Passi has decided to make a change. Fares Bahlouli (Lille) replaces Yassine Benzia.
Ibrahim Amadou goes off the pitch and Yves Bissouma (Lille) comes on.
That's the end of the game for Falcao, who is replaced by Valere Germain (Monaco).
Leonardo Jardim prepares a substitution. Kylian Mbappe is replaced by Benjamin Mendy (Monaco).
Here is an example of luck not being on your side. A slightly disorientated Junior Alonso (Lille) puts the ball into his own net.
Substitution. Joao Moutinho walks off the pitch and Guido Carrillo (Monaco) comes on as a substitute.
That's all for today as the game is over.
The first half has just begun.
Edinson Cavani (Paris SG) finds some space inside the box and powers his header past the goalkeeper, giving him no chance.
This yellow card was deserved. The tackle by Henri Saivet (St Etienne) was quite harsh and Amaury Delerue didn't hesitate to show him a yellow card.
Goal! Lucas (Paris SG) pounced on a loose ball inside the box and beats the goalkeeper with a shot into the top of the net. He makes it 0:2.
The match has reached half-time.
The players are back out on the pitch following the half-time break and the second half is about to start.
The teams are back out for the second half and here is a change on the pitch. Unai Emery gives a chance to Marquinhos (Paris SG) and Thiago Silva is off.

Julian Draxler (Paris SG) must feel embarrassed now. He received a killer pass, but his shot from the six-yard box was a disaster. He miskicked and made it very easy for Stephane Ruffier to get hold of the ball. Paris SG get a corner.
Substitution. Henri Saivet makes his way off the pitch and Benjamin Corgnet (St Etienne) comes on as his replacement.
Substitution. Robert Beric is replaced by Alexander Soderlund (St Etienne).
Goal! Edinson Cavani (Paris SG) is quickest to react to the rebound and stabs the ball into the back of the net. It's 0:3.
Lucas (Paris SG) has a great chance inside the box and puts the ball into the back of the net.
The manager has decided to make a substitution and Lucas walks off the pitch to be replaced by Goncalo Guedes (Paris SG).
A substitution has been made. Marco Verratti is replaced by Giovani Lo Celso (Paris SG).
Christophe Galtier has decided to substitute Kevin Malcuit and he is replaced by Ronael Pierre-Gabriel (St Etienne).
Amaury Delerue shows a yellow card to Giovani Lo Celso (Paris SG) for his blatant foul.

Giovani Lo Celso produces a sweet pass and picks out Julian Draxler (Paris SG) inside the box. He quickly takes a shot which goes into the bottom right corner and leaves the goalkeeper helpless. He makes it 0:5!
That's the end of the match.
The first half of this match is about to start.

Florian Thauvin (Marseille) blows a clear opportunity to score a goal. He was one-on-one with Yoan Cardinale inside the six-yard box and attempted to put the ball into the bottom left corner, but was denied by a great save.
Problems for Rudi Garcia as Florian Thauvin is not able to play anymore. His injury is too serious and Remy Cabella (Marseille) replaces him.

Bafetimbi Gomis (Marseille) outjumps the defenders inside the six-yard box to meet the corner and scores with a header into the middle of the goal. The keeper had no chance to react. The score is now 1:0.
Paul Baysse (Nice) has a goal ruled out for offside!
The foul by Remy Cabella (Marseille) is worthy of a card and a yellow is duly shown by Antony Gautier.
The end of the first half.
The half-time break is over and the second half is about to start.
The whistle blows and Dimitri Payet (Marseille) is booked for an infringement.
It's in the back of the net! Paul Baysse sprays a pass out to Mario Balotelli (Nice), and he has an easy job to slot the ball into an empty net. The score is 1:1.
The referee stops play so that a substitution can be made and Ricardo Pereira departs the field of play to be replaced by Anastasios Donis (Nice).
Hiroki Sakai (Marseille) sees a yellow card. He should be more careful because one more challenge like that could result in a red card.
Dante (Nice) gets booked for the first time in this match.
Patrice Evra (Marseille) gets to the ball and glances a sweet header that goes inside the left post!
Rod Fanni (Marseille) picks up a yellow card.
Rudi Garcia prepares a substitution. Maxime Lopez is replaced by Andre-Frank Zambo Anguissa (Marseille).
The referee stops play so that a substitution can be made and Vincent Koziello leaves the pitch and Mickael Le Bihan (Nice) comes on.
The referee signals that it is time for a substitution and Bassem Srarfi (Nice) will replace Valentin Eysseric.
Rudi Garcia has decided to make a change. Bouna Sarr (Marseille) replaces Remy Cabella.
Yohann Pele (Marseille) is penalised.
That's the end of the match.
The match has just started.
Henrique Dalbert (Nice) can't expect anything else than a yellow card for his hard tackle. And a yellow it is. Ruddy Buquet didn't think twice about pulling it out of his pocket.
Mario Balotelli (Nice) takes a great first touch to control a killer pass on the edge of the box and drills a shot into the bottom left corner in trademark fashion.

Angel Di Maria (Paris SG) receives a quality pass and releases a rocket of a shot from distance, but his amazing effort goes just wide of the right post. The goalkeeper probably wouldn't have saved this one.
Ruddy Buquet shows a yellow card to Jean Michael Seri (Nice), who isn't surprised as the tackle was really hard and late.
The referee blows his whistle for half-time, bringing to a close the first 45 minutes of the match.
The referee blows his whistle to signal the start of the second half.
Half-time substitution. Unai Emery decided to make a change. Maxwell is replaced by Thomas Meunier (Paris SG).
A piece of footballing magic! Ricardo Pereira (Nice) collected a precise pass and fired a shot towards the top left corner, bouncing in off the post. The goalkeeper was helpless.
Yellow card! It's like Thomas Meunier (Paris SG) was asking for a caution with his behaviour. Ruddy Buquet agrees and books him.
Julian Draxler (Paris SG) fouls his opponent and receives a yellow card from the referee, but he is clearly not happy with the decision.
Edinson Cavani (Paris SG) picks up a yellow card.
Goal! Thiago Silva gets up really well from the corner and heads the ball into the six-yard box where Marquinhos (Paris SG) glances a header into the net. 2:1.
The manager has decided to make a substitution and Serge Aurier walks off the pitch to be replaced by Adrien Rabiot (Paris SG).
Thomas Meunier (Paris SG) gets to the rebound on the edge of the penalty area and fires a shot towards the bottom right corner, but Yoan Cardinale gets a hand to it and keeps it out.
Problems for Lucien Favre as Valentin Eysseric is not able to play anymore. His injury is too serious and Anastasios Donis (Nice) replaces him.
We are about to witness a substitution. Mickael Le Bihan (Nice) is replacing Mario Balotelli.
Here is a change. Julian Draxler is going off and Unai Emery gives the last tactical orders to Lucas (Paris SG).
Lucien Favre prepares a substitution. Vincent Koziello is replaced by Mounir Obbadi (Nice).
Thiago Motta (Paris SG) knows that the game is over for him after receiving a red card from the referee for fouling his opponent!
It's a goal! Anastasios Donis (Nice) gets on the end of a pass and it allows him to finish into an empty net with a close-range header. The score has changed to 3:1.
Angel Di Maria (Paris SG) makes a horror tackle on his opponent and the referee sends him off!
That's the end of the match.
The match has just started.
Benjamin Mendy (Monaco) misses a good chance to score. An inch-perfect cross into the box finds Benjamin Mendy (Monaco) who rises for a header, but sends the ball well over the bar.
Andy Delort (Toulouse) finds himself some space around the penalty spot to connect with a fine free kick. His header is slightly mistimed and sails inches past the right post.
The referee had an easy-decision to make. A yellow card is given to Ola Toivonen (Toulouse) for a foul that he committed a little earlier.

What a wasted opportunity by Bernardo Silva (Monaco)! He creates some space for himself inside the penalty box and unleashes a decent strike towards the bottom right corner, but Alban Lafont makes an astonishing save to thwart him.
Tongo Doumbia (Toulouse) is shown a yellow card by the referee for making a challenge on his opponent, but he looks angry with the decision.
Mikael Lesage shows a yellow card to Somalia (Toulouse) for his blatant foul.
Mikael Lesage has ended the first half by blowing the whistle.
Everything is set for the start of the second half.
Ola Toivonen (Toulouse) reacts quickly in the penalty area and scores with aplomb, giving the goalkeeper no chance!

Goal! Joao Moutinho clips a neat ball into the box in the direction of Kamil Glik (Monaco), who jumps highest and steers a bullet header from the centre of the box into the top right corner. Alban Lafont had no chance of stopping that. 1:1.
Goal! Kylian Mbappe (Monaco) pounced on a loose ball inside the penalty area and beats the goalkeeper with a shot into the bottom right corner. He makes it 2:1.
Benjamin Mendy (Monaco) has tested the patience of referee Mikael Lesage and goes into the book for a previous late challenge.
Benjamin Mendy goes off the pitch and Andrea Raggi (Monaco) comes on.
Pascal Dupraz has decided to make a change. Martin Braithwaite (Toulouse) replaces Somalia.
Goal! Thomas Lemar (Monaco) finds some space inside the box to meet a beautiful cross and fires the ball inside the back of the net.
Here is a change. Jimmy Durmaz is going off and Pascal Dupraz gives the last tactical orders to Dodi Lukebakio (Toulouse).
Falcao (Monaco) fires a shot from close range, but he is somehow only able to hit the left post!
It is time for a substitution. Issiaga Sylla (Toulouse) is on for Ola Toivonen.
Kylian Mbappe (Monaco) has a great chance inside the six-yard box, shoots to the bottom left corner, but Alban Lafont pulls off an exquisite save to deny him.
It will be a substitution. Valere Germain (Monaco) is ready to enter the pitch as Kylian Mbappe walks off.
Oscar Trejo (Toulouse) is booked after bringing down an opponent. Mikael Lesage had an easy-decision to make.
Leonardo Jardim has decided to substitute Thomas Lemar and he is replaced by Jorge (Monaco).
There will be no more action in this match as the referee signals full time.
Today's match has just started, enjoy the game!
Thomas Mangani (Angers) has a shot blocked from inside the box. The referee and his assistant both point at the corner flag. Angers will have an opportunity to threaten the opposition's goal.

Anthony Lopes hears the fans clapping his superb goalkeeping. Baptiste Santamaria (Angers) shoots from the edge of the box towards the left side of the goal, but the goalkeeper makes a magnificent save.
Goal! Mathieu Valbuena (Lyon) was in the right place at the right time to get to the rebound inside the box and gleefully rifles the ball low inside the right post. It's 0:1.

Cheikh N'Doye (Angers) has a great chance inside the six-yard box, shoots to the right side of the goal, but Anthony Lopes pulls off an exquisite save to deny him. It will be a corner kick for Angers.
One of the defenders is in the right place at the right time and makes a vital stop to deny a close-range header from Jonathan Bamba (Angers). Angers will have a chance to score from a corner kick.
Cheikh N'Doye (Angers) is unlucky with a goal-bound effort from the edge of the box. A brilliant save by Anthony Lopes stops the ball from going inside right post.
Mathieu Valbuena (Lyon) sees a yellow card from Antony Gautier after he sent one of the opposing players to the ground.
Antony Gautier shows the yellow card to Maxime Gonalons (Lyon) for a heavy challenge.
Nabil Fekir (Lyon) takes the free kick and sends it towards the bottom right corner of the goal, giving the goalkeeper no chance.
Nabil Fekir (Lyon) kept talking out of turn to the referee until Antony Gautier lost patience and pulled out a yellow card.
Antony Gautier has ended the first half by blowing the whistle.
The players are back out on the pitch following the half-time break and the second half is about to start.

Cheikh N'Doye (Angers) jumped highest inside the box to meet a perfectly executed corner kick by Thomas Mangani. His header was precise and ended up inside the left post, leaving the goalkeeper flapping in the wind. The score is 1:2.
Today's referee Antony Gautier rightly decides to book Romain Thomas (Angers) for his harsh tackle.

Alexandre Letellier can hear the fans clapping for his superb goalkeeping after he magnificently stops the close-range effort from Mathieu Valbuena (Lyon). The ball would have probably ended up inside the right post. Lyon have been awarded a corner kick.
That's the end of the game for Famara Diedhiou, who is replaced by Nicolas Pepe (Angers).
Nabil Fekir (Lyon) meets a cross on the edge of the box and produces a header towards the left side of the goal, but one of the defending players blocks the effort.
Baptiste Santamaria is being substituted because of an injury. Stephane Moulin sends Kevin Berigaud (Angers) on the pitch.
Jonathan Bamba (Angers) has a good chance to get on the scoresheet and fires the ball towards goal from the edge of the penalty box, but it goes narrowly over the crossbar.
Karl Toko Ekambi (Angers) latches on to a superb cross inside the box but only hits the crossbar with a fine header. What a chance!
The substitution has been made. Pierrick Capelle (Angers) has replaced Jonathan Bamba.
Bruno Genesio has decided to substitute Mathieu Valbuena and he is replaced by Rachid Ghezzal (Lyon).
Mateo Pavlovic (Angers) receives a red card after his awful challenge. He completely lost his temper and referee Antony Gautier sends him off the pitch.
The main referee, Antony Gautier, is apparently not going to tolerate any discussions. Vincent Manceau (Angers) is given a yellow card for dissent.
Problems for Bruno Genesio as Corentin Tolisso is not able to play anymore. His injury is too serious and Jordan Ferri (Lyon) replaces him.
Substitution. Maxwel Cornet makes way for Rafael (Lyon).
Antony Gautier is looking at his watch and immediately ends this match.
Here we go, today's match is starting right now.
Jordan Ferri (Lyon) is shown a yellow card for a late challenge.
Falcao (Monaco) rises high to head the corner in the net and beyond the goalkeeper.
OFF THE WOODWORK! Bernardo Silva (Monaco) picks up the ball inside the box and produces a snap shot that smashes against the crossbar!
Goal! Kylian Mbappe (Monaco) pounced on a loose ball inside the box and beats the goalkeeper with a shot into the bottom left corner. He makes it 0:2.
Benoit Bastien has ended the first half by blowing the whistle.
Everything is set for the start of the second half.
Goal! The corner is whipped in and Lucas Tousart (Lyon) is in the right place at the right time, planting his header perfectly into the left side of the goal. He makes it 1:2.
Thomas Lemar (Monaco) takes his opponent down and receives a yellow card from the referee.
Rafael (Lyon) is booked after bringing down an opponent. Benoit Bastien had an easy-decision to make.
Substitution. Jean-Philippe Mateta will be replaced by Mathieu Valbuena (Lyon).
Bruno Genesio has decided to substitute Sergi Darder and he is replaced by Houssem Aouar (Lyon).
The referee signals that it is time for a substitution and Maxime Gonalons (Lyon) will replace Jordan Ferri.
Substitution. Kylian Mbappe did his best and is replaced by Valere Germain (Monaco).

What an opportunity! Lucas Tousart (Lyon) squanders a huge opportunity as he latches on to a perfect cross from the wing. He produces a bullet header from around the penalty spot which goes just wide of the left post!
The referee signals that it is time for a substitution and Joao Moutinho (Monaco) comes onto the pitch so that Falcao can be given a rest.
The referee blows his whistle for the final time to end this match.
The referee blows his whistle and we are underway.
The referee can't ignore those comments and Marco Verratti (Paris SG) sees a yellow card for bad language.
Tony Chapron shows a yellow card to Romain Thomas (Angers) for his blatant foul.
Brilliant goal! Angel Di Maria (Paris SG) gets on the scoresheet with a perfectly taken free kick. The ball goes inside the right post.
Goal disallowed! Karl Toko Ekambi (Angers) scores but Tony Chapron blows his whistle for a foul.
The first half of today's match has just finished.
The second half gets underway.
Famara Diedhiou (Angers) commits a nasty foul by bringing down his opponent.
Substitution. Javier Pastore did his best and is replaced by Lucas (Paris SG).
The referee signals that it is time for a substitution and Jonathan Bamba (Angers) comes onto the pitch so that Nicolas Pepe can be given a rest.
Unai Emery has decided to make a change. Thiago Motta (Paris SG) replaces Blaise Matuidi.
The referee stops play so that a substitution can be made and Kevin Berigaud (Angers) replaces Famara Diedhiou.
Angel Di Maria (Paris SG) has acres of space after latching on to a precise pass into the box. He doesn't hesitate to unleash a great effort which ends up in the bottom left corner.
Unai Emery prepares a substitution. Angel Di Maria is replaced by Goncalo Guedes (Paris SG).
Nothing more will happen in this game as the referee blows for full time.
The first half has started.
Alexandre Lacazette (Lyon) rises high to head the corner in the net and beyond the goalkeeper.
This yellow card was deserved. The tackle by Adrien Rabiot (Paris SG) was quite harsh and Clement Turpin didn't hesitate to show him a yellow card.
Edinson Cavani (Paris SG) receives a yellow card for talking out of turn to the referee.
Adrien Rabiot (Paris SG) receives the ball inside the box, reacts quickly and without any problems fires the ball into the back of the net.

Angel Di Maria (Paris SG) is unlucky with a goal-bound effort from the edge of the box. A brilliant save by Anthony Lopes stops the ball from going inside the left post. The ball is out of play. Paris SG will have a chance to score from a corner.
Julian Draxler (Paris SG) connects with a pass inside the box and slams home into the bottom right corner. The goalkeeper was helpless.
Clement Turpin has ended the first half by blowing the whistle.
The half-time break is over and the second half is about to start.
Substitution. Alexandre Lacazette leaves the pitch and is replaced by Sergi Darder (Lyon).
Unai Emery has decided to introduce fresh legs, with Blaise Matuidi (Paris SG) replacing Julian Draxler.
What was Maxime Gonalons (Lyon) thinking? He will not get away with that. The referee shows him a yellow card.
A substitution has been made. Mathieu Valbuena is replaced by Rachid Ghezzal (Lyon).
We are about to witness a subsitution. Maxwel Cornet (Lyon) for Memphis Depay.
Here is a change. Javier Pastore is going off and Unai Emery gives the last tactical orders to Lucas (Paris SG).
The referee signals that it is time for a substitution and Thiago Motta (Paris SG) will replace Marco Verratti.
The referee checks his watch and blows his whistle to signal the end of this match.
The match has just started.
Kylian Mbappe (Monaco) reacts quickly in the penalty area and scores with aplomb, giving the goalkeeper no chance!
Antony Gautier shows a yellow card to Damien Da Silva (Caen) for his blatant foul.
The referee blows his whistle for half-time, bringing to a close the first 45 minutes of the match.
The second half gets underway.
Damien Da Silva (Caen) brings his opponent down. Antony Gautier has a clear sight of it and blows his whistle for a foul. Monaco are given a penalty!
Fabinho (Monaco) confidently powers his spot-kick into the left side of the goal.
Substitution. Damien Da Silva leaves the pitch and is replaced by Jean-Victor Makengo (Caen).
A substitution has been made. Yann Karamoh goes off and Jeff Louis (Caen) comes on.
Leonardo Jardim has decided to introduce fresh legs, with Tiemoue Bakayoko (Monaco) replacing Valere Germain.
Kylian Mbappe (Monaco) scores from quite a difficult position as he leaps high to connect with a cross and powers his header inside the left post. Excellent finish.
The referee stops play so that a substitution can be made and Thomas Lemar departs the field of play to be replaced by Bernardo Silva (Monaco).
Fabinho (Monaco) missed a big chance! He produces a stunning volley from inside the box, but his effort goes not far wide of the right post.
Leonardo Jardim has decided to substitute Kylian Mbappe and he is replaced by Irvin Cardona (Monaco).
That's the end of the match.
The referee blows his whistle and we are underway.
It's an own goal! A pitiful moment for Benjamin Jeannot (Lorient), who tries to clear a cross into the six-yard box from the corner but instead sends the ball behind his own keeper. The score is 0:1.
There will be nothing more to see in the first half. The whistle blowing of Tony Chapron has ended it.
Everything is set for the start of the second half.

Edinson Cavani looks around to decide who he is going to pass to. He picks out Christopher Nkunku (Paris SG) who receives the ball perfectly and unleashes a terrific low strike from long range. The ball finds its way towards the middle of the goal and ends behind the surprised goalkeeper. The score is now 0:2.
Substitution. Benjamin Jeannot walks off the pitch and Jeremie Aliadiere (Lorient) comes on as a substitute.

Michael Ciani (Lorient) jumps highest to meet the ball from the corner kick and finishes behind the helpless keeper with a fine header inside the right post. The defence stare motionlessly at each other. What a peach of a goal that is. Michael Ciani (Lorient) has every right to celebrate!
Steven Moreira (Lorient) violates the laws of the game and is shown a yellow card by the referee, but it could have been a straight red as well.
The game is interrupted. Christopher Nkunku (Paris SG) is given a yellow card. He has to be more careful now.
Unai Emery is forced to make a change. Thomas Meunier is unable to continue due to injury, Serge Aurier (Paris SG) comes on.
Mathieu Peybernes (Lorient) picked up a yellow card for saying too much to the referee.
We are about to witness a subsitution. Pierre Yves Hamel (Lorient) for Arnold Mvuemba.
Unai Emery prepares a substitution. Julian Draxler is replaced by Hatem Ben Arfa (Paris SG).
The match has just finished.
Here we go, today's match is starting right now.
Fabinho (Monaco) is shown a yellow card by the referee for making a challenge on his opponent, but he looks angry with the decision.
Ruddy Buquet has ended the first half by blowing the whistle.
The players are back out on the pitch following the half-time break and the second half is about to start.
Kylian Mbappe (Monaco) meets a cross and produces a header towards the bottom left corner, but one of the defending players blocks the effort.
Here comes a substitution. Thomas Lemar is given a rest as he is replaced by Falcao (Monaco).
Goal Kylian Mbappe (Monaco)! Kylian Mbappe (Monaco) was put through by Falcao and he showed brilliant composure inside the box to bury the ball into the back of the net. 1:0.
After receiving a beautiful pass, Joao Moutinho (Monaco) had a huge opportunity. He coolly unleashed a perfect shot, which went towards the top left corner, bouncing in off the post.
Here's the change. Valere Germain leaves the pitch and Nabil Dirar (Monaco) comes on as a substitute.
We are about to witness a subsitution. Diego Rolan (Bordeaux) for Gaetan Laborde.
Jocelyn Gourvennec decides to make a substitution. Valentin Vada will be replaced by Jeremy Menez (Bordeaux).
We are about to witness a substitution. Adam Ounas (Bordeaux) is replacing Malcom.
Substitution. Bernardo Silva makes way for Tiemoue Bakayoko (Monaco).
Goal! It's a catastrophic error from the opponent which has gifted a chance to Diego Rolan (Bordeaux), who rolls the ball into the back of the net from close range. 2:1.
Jeremy Menez (Bordeaux) is the one who receives a yellow card.
Milan Gajic (Bordeaux) earns the yellow card.
The yellow card is received by Nicolas Pallois (Bordeaux).
That's it for today, Ruddy Buquet has blown his whistle and the game is over.
The first half of this match is about to start.
Goal! Kylian Mbappe (Monaco) was in the right place at the right time to get to the rebound inside the box and gleefully rifles the ball low inside the right post. It's 1:0.
A yellow card for a tackle by Felipe Pardo (Nantes). Mikael Lesage doesn't hesitate at all to make this decision.
Valere Germain (Monaco) converts a killer cross with a strong and precise shot that goes across the goal and past the goalkeeper.
The foul by Jemerson (Monaco) is worthy of a card and a yellow is duly shown by Mikael Lesage.

Bernardo Silva showcases his great technique and produces a beautiful lofted cross into the box. Kylian Mbappe (Monaco) meets the cross and gets himself onto the scoresheet with a header into the bottom left corner. It's 3:0.
The first half of today's match has just finished.
Everything is set for the start of the second half.
Sergio Conceicao has decided to substitute Adrien Thomasson and he is replaced by Amine Harit (Nantes).
Great ball in from Benjamin Mendy. Valere Germain (Monaco) should really have done better with a close-range header, but he heads it a whisker wide of the right post.
Emiliano Sala (Nantes) is unlucky with a goal-bound effort from the edge of the box. A brilliant save by Danijel Subasic stops the ball from hitting the bottom left corner.
Fabinho (Monaco) smoothly converts the penalty with a beautiful low drive into the right side of the goal.
It is time for a substitution. Yacine Bammou (Nantes) is on for Felipe Pardo.
Sergio Conceicao prepares a substitution. Emiliano Sala is replaced by Jules Iloki (Nantes).
Kylian Mbappe (Monaco) shoots from the edge of the penalty area. The ball travels towards the bottom left corner, but Maxime Dupe easily deals with the threat.
